    <h2>The 'How'</h2>
    <p>It's a lovely exercise to reflect on some gratitude for all the people who make the things that you use to make things.</p>
    <p>Here's a (certainly incomplete) list of things that I make use of in order to build this website:</p>
    <p>I use {% ext "https://neovim.io/" %}neovim{% endext %} and {% ext "https://www.sublimetext.com/" %}Sublime Text{% endext %} to write in (both code and content).</p>
    <p>I use {% ext "https://iterm2.com/" %}iTerm{% endext %} as my terminal.</p>
    <p>Once I write stuff, it gets version-controlled in {% ext "https://github.com/" %}Github{% endext %}, from which it's published to the internet through {% ext "https://www.netlify.com/" %}Netlify{% endext %}.</p>
    <p>My runtime environment is {% ext "https://nodejs.org/en/" %}Node.js{% endext %}, with {% ext "https://www.npmjs.com/" %}NPM{% endext %} managing the packages.</p>
    <p>The site is generated using {% ext "https://www.11ty.dev/" %}Eleventy{% endext %} using the {% ext "https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/" %}Nunjucks{% endext %} templating engine, with {% ext "https://sass-lang.com/" %}SCSS{% endext %} to build my styles. I'm using {% ext "https://esbuild.github.io/" %}esbuild{% endext %} to bundle my JavaScript libraries (although any JS I write myself I leave un-minified so you can read it yourself). I use {% ext "https://postcss.org/" %}PostCSS{% endext %} to run {% ext "https://github.com/postcss/autoprefixer" %}Autoprefixer{% endext %} and {% ext "https://purgecss.com/" %}PurgeCSS{% endext %}.</p>
    <p>The site uses {% ext "https://alpinejs.dev/" %}Alpine.js{% endext %} to help with passing state data between elements, {% ext "https://fusejs.io/" %}Fuse.js{% endext %} for fuzzy searching, {% ext "https://prismjs.com/" %}Prism{% endext %} to highlight code, {% ext "https://github.com/rough-stuff/rough-notation" %}Rough Notation {% endext %} to "sketchily" underline and highlight text, Paul Irish's {% ext "https://github.com/paulirish/lite-youtube-embed" %}Lite YouTube Embed{% endext %} for video "facades", and {% ext "https://instant.page/" %}instant.page{% endext %} for preloading links.</p>
    <p>To see how I'm doing, I check my work in {% ext "https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse" %}Lighthouse{% endext %}, {% ext "https://www.deque.com/axe/browser-extensions/" %}axe DevTools{% endext %}, {% ext "https://accessibilityinsights.io/" %}Accessibility Insights{% endext %}, developer tools in {% ext "https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/" %}Chrome{% endext %}, {% ext "https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html" %}Firefox{% endext %}, and {% ext "https://developer.apple.com/safari/" %}Safari{% endext %}, {% ext "https://github.com/tbroadley/spellchecker-cli" %}spellchecker-cli{% endext %} and {% ext "https://github.com/amperser/proselint" %}proselint{% endext %}.</p>
